#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:5
msgid "The ``Configure - KStars`` window allows you to modify a wide range of display options. You can access the window with the ``Configure toolbar`` icon, or by selecting the ``Settings`` â†’ ``Configure KStars...`` menu item. The window is depicted below:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:10
msgid "|Configure - KStars Window|"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:12
msgid "The ``Configure - KStars`` window is divided into fourteen pages: ``Catalogs``, ``Solar System``, ``Satellites``, ``Supernovae``, ``Guides``, ``Terrain``, ``Image Overlays``, ``Colors``, ``FITS``, ``INDI``, ``Ekos``, ``Xplanet``, ``Advanced`` and ``Developer``."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:17
msgid "In the ``Catalogs`` page, you determine several properties concerning the display of the star and deep sky object catalogs."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:21
msgid "In the ``Solar System`` page, you can specify whether the Sun, Moon, planets, comets and asteroids are displayed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:24
msgid "The ``Satellites`` page allows you to set the satellites view options."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:27
msgid "The ``Supernovae`` page allows you to manage how supernovae are displayed by KStars."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:30
msgid "The ``Guides`` page lets you toggle whether non-objects are displayed (i.e., constellation lines, constellation names, the Milky Way contour)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:34
msgid "It is possible to choose a ``Sky culture``: for the constellation lines and names on this page. The current version of KStars includes data for more than a dozen sky cultures."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:39
msgid "The ``Terrain page`` allows you to set the terrain or landscape image and configure its speedup options."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:42
msgid "The ``Image Overlays`` page allows you to add and manage your own images that will be displayed in the skymap."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:45
msgid "The ``Colors`` page allows you to set the color scheme, and to define new custom color schemes."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:48
msgid "For detailed explanation of the options on the ``FITS`` page see the :doc:`Configure FITS  <fits-configure>` section."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:51
msgid "For detailed explanation of the options on the ``INDI`` page see the :doc:`Configure INDI  <indi-configure>` section."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:54
msgid "For detailed explanation of ``Ekos`` astrophotography suite, see the :doc:`Ekos section of this manual  <ekos>`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:57
msgid "The ``Xplanet`` page provides fine-grained control over `Solar system planet surface renderer Xplanet <http://xplanet.sourceforge.net/>`__ (should be installed separately)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:62
msgid "The ``Advanced`` page provides fine-grained control over the more subtle behaviors of KStars."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/viewops.rst:65
msgid "The ``Developer`` page allows you to enable or disable a few options mostly useful for developers or for folks looking to help debug issues. Currently these are enabling the saving of images during Ekos's autofocus, guiding and alignment."
msgstr ""

